description: Number of primes between consecutive 5th powers.
links: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n=0,...,82
example: a(1)=11 the number of primes between 32=2^5 and 1=1^5.
prog: (PARI) { default(primelimit, 4294965247); for (n=0, 82, write("b062517.txt", n, " ", primepi((n + 2)^5) - primepi((n + 1)^5)) ) } [From _Harry J. Smith_, Aug 08 2009]
author: _Labos Elemer_, Jul 10 2001
